window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Don’t breathe. Don’t move. Don’t make a sound. And whatever you do, don’t trust a soul. Because in this thrilling collection of heart-stopping original stories, anyone can be a villain, and no one is who – or what – he or she seems. From 13 masters of adult and young-adult thriller writing, including six <i>New York Times</i> best-selling authors, here are stories guaranteed to keep you on the edge of your seat and up all night.</p> <p>Edited by best-selling author R. L. Stine, and read by a talented cast of narrators, <i>Fear</i> contains 13 stories of suspense and horror by Meg Cabot, Heather Brewer, Jennifer Allison, Ryan Brown, Alane Ferguson, Heather Graham, Peg Kehret, Tim Maleeny, James Rollins, Walter Sorrells, Suzanne Weyn, and F. Paul Wilson.</p>"; 
